<P>
   BOOK-NOTES _ Four years ago, Birmingham attorney Mike Stewart
took a deep breath and a Tagamet and resigned as general counsel
for a large healthcare company to write a novel. After eight months
of 12-hour days, Stewart signed a lucarative contract with Putnam
for a mystery, ``Sins of the Brother.'' Now Hollywood is calling
and Stewart is finishing his second novel, ``Dog Island.''
(O'Briant, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20.
