   TRAVEL-SKI _ TELLURIDE, Colo. _ I had come to this Telluride,
Colo. _ once a rowdy mining colony, now an elegantly rustic retreat
for such celebs as Oprah Winfrey and Tom Cruise _ to learn how to
snowboard. It would turn out to be the most strenuous thing I've
ever done in the name of leisure activity. (Hamilton, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   Eds: Embargoed for Sunday, Dec. 9.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   TELLURIDE _ TELLURIDE, Colo. _ A visit to the town of Telluride,
Colo.: The floozies and gold rushers are long gone, replaced by
Wall Street refugees and Hollywood types escaping the glare of
Tinseltown. The bordellos are now historic landmarks, the saloons
serve up microbrews and Absolut. The bank where Butch Cassidy
pulled off his first armed robbery in 1889 is now a boutique that
sells pricey ski togs.(Hamilton, Atlanta Journal-Constitution.)
WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   Eds: Embargoed for Sunday, Dec. 9.
</P>
