   ENDOFAFFAIR _ Quick, check your calendar. Seeing Neil Jordan's
The End of the Affair, you will swear you've been transported back
to the 1940s, for the atmosphere of Graham Greene's wartime London
novel has been re-created so authentically. Then check your watch,
because you'll swear as well that this is one of the longest, least
involving movies under two hours. (Erstein, Palm Beach Post). 45.
