<P>
   TURTLE-LADY (South Padre Island, Texas) _ Ila Loetscher, who was
known
</P>
<P>
   as the ``Turtle Lady'' for decades of nursing sick sea turtles
behind her beachfront home, died after a long illness. She was 95.
But relatives, friends and area officials say her work to rescue
stranded sea turtles and teach children about their plight _
especially the endangered Kemps Ridley _ will continue, and they
are planning a large turtle recovery facility. By JAMES PINKERTON.
(Photo available on NYT database).
</P>
<P>
   PATAKI-TEACHERS (Albany, N.Y.) _ In a State of the State address
laden with education initiatives, New York Gov. George Pataki said
50,000 new teachers could be lured to work in New York's neediest
schools by offering free public university tuition and discounts at
private colleges. By JAMES M. ODATO.
</P>
