<P>
   WOMEN-VOTE (Washington) _ So far in this election campaign, the
gender gap that has aided Democrats in the past is not a political
albatross for Texas Gov. George W. Bush. In a new poll by Emily's
List, which raises campaign cash for pro-choice Democratic women
candidates, Bush ran one percentage point ahead of Vice President
Al Gore among women voters and dead even with former Sen. Bill
Bradley. By DAN FREEDMAN.
