<P>
   DVD-BOOM (Undated) _ An estimated 4 million DVD (digital
versatile disc) players, many priced at $300 or less, were sold
last year, vastly exceeding industry projections. The surge in
sales suggests that the new technology is not only catching on,
where other innovations like laser discs did not, but is also
likely to overtake VHS in a few years as the home entertainment
format of choice. Analysts and retailers say that the growing
popularity of DVD is also expected to reinvigorate the video retail
business by giving customers a new reason to visit the video store.
By Terry Pristin.
