500 was up 0.14 percent but the Nasdaq composite index was down
1.42 percent. Treasury prices were slightly higher, with the yield
on the 30-year bond at 6.60 percent. European markets were largely
lower, with London down 1.44 percent and Frankfurt nearly flat. In
Asia, the Nikkei closed down 2.02 percent, and Hong Kong's Hang
Seng index ended down 4.38 percent. By Robert D. Hershey Jr..
