</P>
<P>
   If you have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the
Cox News Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   BASEBALL
</P>
<P>
   BBN-ROCKER _ Major League Baseball has ordered Atlanta Braves
pitcher John Rocker to undergo psychological testing after his
disparaging remarks about homosexuals and minorities. Commissioner
Bud Selig says he'll wait to see the results of the tests before
deciding how to punish the Braves reliever. (Stinson, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 16. WITH PHOTOS
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Developing from 5 p.m. Braves press conference.
</P>
<P>
   FOOTBALL/NFL PLAYOFFS
</P>
<P>
   TITANS _ A look at the Tennessee Titans fever. New stadium, new
team, city new to playoffs. (Schlabach, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 22.
</P>
<P>
   FOOTBALL/COLLEGES
</P>
<P>
   NCSTATE-COACH _ Florida State assistant Chuck Amato returned to
his alma mater when he was hired Thursday as the new football coach
at North Carolina State. Georgia Tech offensive coordinator Ralph
Friedgen had campaigned for the job. (Clemons, Atlanta
Journal-Consti. 10.
</P>
<P>
   BASKETBALL
</P>
<P>
   BKN-CARTER-JORDAN _ The comparisons to Michael Jordan began last
season for Vince Carter, but this year his play has been
reminiscent of the former Chicago Bulls star. Carter is among the
NBA leaders in scoring, but he's easily the league's most exciting
player with his array of high-flying dunks. Carter and the Raptors
will face the Hawks Friday at Philips Arena. (Bunn, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 22.
</P>
<P>
   GOLF
</P>
<P>
   GOLF-PREVIEW _ The message is coming through loud and clear.
Those who want to successfully compete against Tiger Woods better
make some major changes to keep Woods from running away with the
sport. The best example for the 2000 season comes from David Duval,
No. 2 in the world. A chiseled Duval showed up last week about 35
pounds lighter than when we last saw him. (Sheeley, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 22.
</P>
