   &QL; 
CLINTON (Washington) - President Bill Clinton will visit Arizona on
Monday to make a ``major environmental announcement,`` apparently
about the creation of four national monuments, including a new,
one-million acre monument on the North Rim of the Grand Canyon.
These monuments were recommended by Secretary of the Interior Bruce
Babbitt but opposed by Arizona's GOP delegation because they had
not been consulted and believed it should be a congressional
matter. By JEFF BARKER. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
