<P>
   TLC-GRAMMYS (Seattle) _ TLC's Rozanda ``Chilli'' Thomas insists
that ``No Scrubs,'' the song that earned the pop/R&AMP;B vocal trio two
of six Grammy nominations this week, isn't an anti-guy diatribe.
``It's about this guy who has no life. He won't take care of his
kids, he has no intention of getting a job. He's a leech.'' Thomas
said. ``A lot of guys have friends like that. That's why I like to
stress that it's not a male-bashing song. It's about a certain type
of guy.'' ``No Scrubs'' is one of the strongest message songs in
TLC's 10-year career.
</P>
