think he wouldn't try to top it with another biographical movie
about another famous black martyr for decades to come. But here he
is in ``The Hurricane'' playing Rubin ``Hurricane'' Carter, the New
Jersey middleweight boxing championship contender who was
railroaded into prison in the early '60s and spent close to two
decades trying to prove his innocence.
</P>
<P>
   By William Arnold. (Story has moved in the ``e'' category.)
