<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-LAKERNOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
RICE: `JUST ANOTHER GAME'
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ In three years with the Charlotte Hornets, Glen
Rice became an All-Star Game MVP, an All-NBA second-team selection
and the league's top 3-point shooter (.470 in 1997). He had his
best scoring year, 26.8 points per game in 1996-97, and led the
Hornets to the Eastern Conference semifinals in '98.
</P>
<P>
   But as the Los Angeles Lakers prepared to play the Hornets
tonight _ for the first time since the March 1999 trade that
brought Rice to L.A. _ he tried to downplay the reunion.
</P>
<P>
   ``Looking forward to it?'' Rice said, repeating a reporter's
question.``It's just another game. Just another game.''
</P>
<P>
   The Hornets parted with Rice after deciding they would not meet
his demands for a rich new contract. But he said there will be no
emotional reaction to playing his former team.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's just a team that's in our way of success, and we've just
got to go out there and play against them,'' he said. ``If you go
in there and if you get too emotionally caught up in it, then you
won't perform well, and we don't need that at this point.''
</P>
<P>
   But Rice admitted it was difficult to leave the Hornets,
``especially with the success I had in Charlotte,'' and in light of
the contract dispute. But, he insisted, ``I don't even think about
that anymore. That's just something that happened, and we've just
got to move on. That's just part of the business.... ``We're on top
right now, and that's a great feeling. I don't think about
Charlotte. I think about what the Lakers have to do.''
</P>
<P>
   Fishy shooting: Derek Fisher is doing everything short of
collecting rabbit's feet to shake a shooting slump that's dropped
his field-goal percentage to .315.
</P>
<P>
   He stayed 30 minutes after Wednesday night's victory over the
Clippers and came 45 minutes early to Thursday's practice to work
on his ailing jumpshot. Fisher went 1 for 16 in the two games
against the Clippers and is 2 for 30 over his last five games.
</P>
<P>
   ``The shots just don't feel good,'' he said. ``I mean, I'm
getting good shots and everything is OK, but they just don't feel
good.... ``I don't feel bad, or like I'm playing poorly, as long as
I'm doing some of the other things, I can live with not shooting
well. But if I start slacking in some of the other areas, then I've
really got a problem.''
</P>
<P>
   The Lakers' 12-game winning streak has made the slump a little
easier to bear, and Fisher continues to contribute with defense and
hustle.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm just glad we're winning while I'm doing this,'' he said
with a laugh. ``You know, if I was doing this while we were losing,
everybody would be saying I'm the reason why the Lakers can't win.
But winning a lot of times sweeps things under the rug.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
