Baselitz's ``Man of Faith.'' Lieberman, 75, is frequently
criticized for ignoring American masters in favor of British ones.
Asked about a British bias, Lieberman denied that he has one.
``People say it because they hear other people say it,'' he
replies. ``I'm sorry. That's the reason.'' (Angel Franco/The New
York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT20) NEW YORK -- Jan. 6, 2000 -- ADV. FOR SUN., JAN. 9 --
METROPOLITAN-MUSEUM-1 -- The director of Metropolitan Museum of
Art, Philippe de Montebello in front of Japers Johns' ``White
Flag.'' Virtually since it opened in 1870, the Met has been accused
of snubbing the art of the present. ``I don't hate contemporary
art. You'd have to be stupid to say yes to that question,'' says de
Montebello. ``But what I object to is the tyrannical attitude of
too many people in the contemporary art world, who are so insecure
that they think that a divergence of opinion about a work of art
signifies hostility to the whole field.'' (Angel Franco/The New
York Times)
</P>
