calls Bush ``governor smirk,'' and sees Senator John McCain as the
``Harrison Ford 'Air Force One' candidate,'' running on image
instead of substance. While stating that Forbes's endorsement was
not a ``hard call,'' McQuaid adds that ``he's dry as toast.''
(Frank O'Brien/The Boston Globe)
