<P>
   (NYT4) NEW YORK -- Jan. 6, 2000 -- ADV. FOR SUN., JAN. 9 --
WRONG-MOUNTAIN-THEATER -- David Hirson on the set of his second
play, ``Wrong Mountain,'' prepares to open on Thursday, at the
Eugene O'Neill Theater. Hirson's play has a contemporary setting,
and is the story of Henry Dennett, 60, an embittered, unappreciated
poet who, infuriated by the presumption of his ex-wife's new
boyfriend, a popular playwright named Guy Halperin, makes a bet
that he can write a play and have it produced. (Sara Krulwich/The
New York Times)
