<P>
   (NYT1) NEW YORK -- Jan. 05, 2000 -- NY-CREW-EDUC -- Rudy Crew,
the outgoing chancellor of the New York City Board of Education,
during an interview Tuesday, his last day as leader of the nation's
largest public school system. Crew says that though he acceded to
the demands of Mayor Rudolph Giuliani on any number of issues, the
dispute with the mayor over whether public school students should
get vouchers to attend private schools was one on which he refused
to negotiate. And that, he believes, was his downfall. (Ruby
Washington/The New York Times)
