<SLUG> BC-EDITORS-NOTE-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES EDITOR'S NOTE FOR FRIDAY, JAN. 7
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: This editor's note will appear in The New York Times on
Friday. Days and dates refer to the original article's transmission
by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be adjusted by
NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-RUSSIA-CHECHNYA-NYT (moved on Wednesday, Dec. 15)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, Dec.
15, about a Russian attack on Grozny, the capital of Chechnya,
cited a report by Maria Eismont of Reuters saying that she had
counted more than 100 dead Russians at the end of a three-hour
battle. The Russian death toll was the largest reported for any
single battle of the war in Chechnya, and in further reporting on
it, The Times asked Reuters if Ms. Eismont had personally counted
that many bodies.
</P>
<P>
   In response, Reuters transmitted an article on Wednesday that
quoted Ms. Eismont as saying, ``There were certainly that many, but
I did not count them all myself.'' The Reuters article said that
Ms. Eismont felt certain that in a telephone conversation with the
Reuters office in Moscow on the day of the battle, she had made it
clear that her report on the death toll reflected accounts from
other correspondents as well as her own.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
