<HEADLINE>
DANNY AIELLO REMAINS DEDICATED TO HIS MOTHER
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: What is the marital status of Danny Aiello? In his series
``Dellaventura,'' he referred to his character's deceased wife as
Frances, and one of his movies is dedicated to Frances Aiello. _
J.M.S., Punta Gorda, Fla.
</P>
<P>
   A: Danny Aiello met his future wife, Sandy, when both were
teen-agers living in the Bronx in New York, and they have been
married for 44 years. They have four children.
</P>
<P>
   Frances Aiello, the mother of the 66-year-old actor, died in
1988. ``My mother was everything to me,'' he told ``People'' in
1990.
</P>
<P>
   The Frances Aiello Day Treatment Center, a Brooklyn, N.Y.,
facility that teaches life skills to people with developmental
disabilities, was named in her honor in 1991.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where can I find the Bed Buddy microwave heat pack, which is
excellent for the aches and pains of arthritis? _ K.E.J., Graham,
Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: That product didn't turn up in a search, but you may be
interested in another heating pad warmed in a microwave.
</P>
<P>
   Body First, a therapeutic massage company in Manhattan, Kan.,
sells a handmade pad filled with jasmine rice. The cost is $20,
plus $5 shipping and handling.
</P>
<P>
   ``You have to be careful when buying microwave heat packs,
because ones made with wheat or barley ... can burn up in the
microwave quicker than ones made with rice,'' said Doug Sellers,
Body First's owner.
</P>
<P>
   To order, call (785) 587-8300 or write to Body First, 2316
Anderson Ave., Manhattan, KS 66502. The company's Web site is
www.bodyfirst.com.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Has the young actress who plays Kimberly on ``The Bold and
the Beautiful'' been on anything else? She looks familiar, but I
can't remember from where. _ F.L., Arlington, texas
</P>
<P>
   A: Ashley Lyn Cafagna, 16, was on ``Saved by the Bell: The New
Class'' for two years and was a guest star on ``Seventh Heaven''.
</P>
<P>
   After winning a talent search contest at age 11, Ashley appeared
in an LA Gear commercial and the film ``Lord of Illusions.'' You
can write to her at 3518 W. Cahuenga Blvd., Suite 202, Los Angeles,
CA 90068.
</P>
<P>
   She also has a Web site at www.ashleycafagna.com, which features
her religious writing and a monthly Bible verse.  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
 &QL; 
.MDRV/ nn
</P>
